constant Rough : obj → Prop
constant White : obj → Prop
constant Big : obj → Prop
constant Red : obj → Prop

axiom T1 : Furry Anne

axiom R2 : ∀ x : obj, White x ∧ Quiet x → Big x
axiom R3 : ∀ x : obj, Big x ∧ Red x → Rough x
axiom R4 : ∀ x : obj, Big x ∧ Red x → Quiet x

axiom R7 : ∀ x : obj, Red x → Round x
axiom R8 : ∀ x : obj, Furry x ∧ Round x → Big x

output:
theorem harry_is_not_white : ¬ White Harry :=
begin
  intro H,
  have H1 : Rough Harry := R1 Harry ⟨T7, H⟩,
  have H2 : Big Harry := R3 Harry ⟨T7, H1⟩,
  have H3 : Furry Harry := R5 Harry ⟨H2, H1⟩,
  have H4 : White Harry := R6 Harry ⟨H2, H3⟩,
  have H5 : ¬ White Harry := (λ H6 : White Harry, (R4 Harry ⟨H2, T7⟩) H1),
  exact H5 H4,
end
